1 c. If an order prohibiting contact is issued upon a charge or arrest, the order
2 terminates upon dismissal, acquittal, sentence, or order deferring imposition of
3 sentence. Upon sentence or order deferring imposition of sentence, the court
4 may issue a new order under this subsection.
5 2. If the court has probable cause to believe that the individual charged or
6 arrestedsubject to an order under subsection 1 is likely to use, display, or threaten to
7 use a firearm or dangerous weapon as defined in section 12.1-01-04 in any further act
8 of violence, the court shall require that the individual surrender for safekeeping any
9 firearm or specified dangerous weapon in or subject to the individual's immediate
10 possession or control, to the sheriff of the county or chief of police of the city in which
11 the individual resides.
12 3. WheneverIf an order prohibiting contact is issued, modified, extended, or terminated
13 under this section, the clerk of court shall forward a copy of the order within one
14 business day to the appropriate law enforcement agency specified in the order. Upon
15 receipt of the copy of the order, the law enforcement agency shall enter the order in
16 the central warrant information system and the national crime information center
17 database provided by the federal bureau of investigation, or its successor agency.
18 a. Once the bureau, after consultation with the state court administrator, determines
19 and implements a method to transmit electronically to the bureau an order
20 prohibiting contact, the court electronically shall send the full text of the order as
21 issued, modified, extended, or terminated in accordance with this section and any
22 data fields identified by the bureau. This electronic submission will fulfill the law
23 enforcement agency's requirement to enter the order in the central warrant
24 information system, but will not fulfill its requirement to enter, maintain, and
25 respond to inquiries regarding the order in the national crime information center
26 database provided by the federal bureau of investigation, or its successor
27 agency.
28 b. Once the bureau, after consultation with the state court administrator, determines
29 and implements an electronic method to notify law enforcement about the order,
30 the clerk of court's requirement to forward the order to the law enforcement
31 agency will be satisfied.
