12 4. An individual who violates a court order issued under this section is guilty of a class A
13 misdemeanor.
14 5. A law enforcement officer shall arrest an individual without a warrant if the officer
15 determines there is probable cause that the individual has committed the offense of
16 violating an order prohibiting contact under this section, whether or not the violation
17 was committed in the presence of the officer. A law enforcement officer who acts in
18 good faith on probable cause and without malice is immune from any civil or criminal
19 liability for making an arrest under this subsection.
20 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Subsection 1 of section 12.1-32-02 of the North Dakota
21 Century Code is amended and reenacted as follows:
22 1. a. Every person convicted of an offense who is sentenced by the court must be
23 sentenced to one or a combination of the following alternatives, unless the
24 sentencing alternatives are otherwise specifically provided in the statute defining
25 the offense or sentencing is deferred under subsection 4:
26 a. (1) Payment of the reasonable costs of the person's prosecution.
27 b. (2) Probation.
28 c. (3) A term of imprisonment, including intermittent imprisonment:
29 (1) (a) In a state correctional facility in accordance with section 29-27-07, in a
30 regional corrections center, or in a county jail, if convicted of a felony
31 or a class A misdemeanor.
